java`\n\nIt exercises the supported constructor path and verifies the public JUL level parsing behavior, but the two legacy `KnownLevelBuilder.add(...)` call sites remain unreachable on the current supported JDK without violating the constraints.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_061ae871c3261499016a23839ca8ac8194863679ddf023648b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 40656, "output": 858, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41514, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780712334798, "responseId": "resp_061ae871c3261499016a23838fb2e48194ba68ae8bb9c6f00b"}}
